    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Turbine_and_Solar_Panel_Repair_16jHo000000L2Ib</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic covers user queries related to issues with wind turbines and solar panels, such as performance inconsistencies, system malfunctions, and repair diagnostics.</description>
        <developerName>Turbine_and_Solar_Panel_Repair_16jHo000000L2Ib</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always offer the customer an upgraded support plan to ensure proactive maintenance and faster issue resolution in the future.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always send a follow-up email to the customer summarizing the status and resolution steps taken, whether software updates or repair arrangements.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Before proceeding further, contact the Release Deployment team to verify if there are any known software or firmware issues affecting the customer&apos;s system version. If a software issue is identified, apologize to the customer and inform them that a patch with the necessary fix will be deployed within the next few days.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>First, ensure the customer has followed all basic troubleshooting steps, such as rebooting the system, checking connections, and inspecting system settings, before moving to service escalation.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Keep detailed notes in the case comments, including the investigation steps, findings, and resolutions. Use Einstein Draft a Case Summary to efficiently summarize key points for the case closure.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the customer has not provided the firmware version of their wind turbine or solar panel system, always ask them to check and provide this information. Knowing the version helps identify compatibility or update-related issues.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the customer agrees to proceed with repair, schedule an on-site technician visit for diagnostics and repairs.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_7</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 7</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the problem is determined to be hardware-related, check the product&apos;s warranty status. If the product is out of warranty and lacks a support plan, inform the customer of the flat-rate repair or replacement cost based on the affected components.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_8</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 8</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If firmware information is unavailable, ask the customer to inspect for visible physical damage, such as cracks in solar panels, corrosion, loose connections, or wear on turbine components. Physical damage often points to hardware-related issues.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_9</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 9</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
