    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Billing_16jHo000000L2Ib</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic encompasses everything related to the handling of payments. It includes addressing billing inquiries and resolving any discrepancies in invoicing and payments.</description>
        <developerName>Billing_16jHo000000L2Ib</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the investigation confirms a billing error, the agent should take appropriate corrective actions. This may involve issuing a credit, adjusting the bill, or reissuing a corrected invoice. On the other hand, if the bill is accurate, the agent should clearly explain the charges to the customer and provide any necessary documentation to support the explanation.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a billing discrepancy arises, the first step is to gather key information, such as the invoice number, billing period, the amount in question, and any supporting documentation the customer can provide.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The agent should review customer&apos;s billing history to locate the relevant bill or transaction. The agent should carefully cross-check the bill against service agreements, promotions, or payment plans to identify potential errors such as double charges, incorrect rates, or missing payments. Additionally, the agent should confirm whether any prior adjustments or corrections have already been made.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Once the issue is resolved, it’s essential to document the interaction, including the nature of the issue, findings, and the steps taken to resolve it. Finally, the agent should follow up with the customer to confirm their satisfaction, providing a summary of the resolution and any adjustments made, either through email or a formal notification.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
        <localDeveloperName>Billing</localDeveloperName>
        <masterLabel>Billing</masterLabel>
        <pluginType>Topic</pluginType>
        <scope>Your job is to help with all aspects of payment processing and billing, including handling billing queries, resolving invoice discrepancies, and processing payments.</scope>
